# quack-auth project conventions

**Source of truth** for coding and layout conventions in this repo.

When the Developer states a **new convention** (or you extend an existing section here):

1. Update **this file** with the full convention text.
2. Add a **one-line pointer** in [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) only — do not duplicate detail there.
3. **Update related Docusaurus docs in the same branch/PR** — **required**, not optional. See [Convention → docs map](#convention--docs-map) below and [`.cursor/rules/docusaurus-docs.mdc`](./docusaurus-docs.mdc). Run `pnpm nx build DOCS` after doc edits.

### Convention → docs map

| Convention area | Update these docs (minimum) |
| --------------- | --------------------------- |
| FE (HTTP client, styling, store, routing, …) | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/frontend.md` |
| BE (modules, filters, validation, routes, …) | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/backend.md` |
| Mongoose / DB | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/mongodb.md` |
| Shared libs (`libs/dtos`, `libs/qu-constants`, `BE_ROUTES`, …) | Relevant `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/*.md` **and** setup page if cross-cutting (e.g. `06-nestjs-zod.md`) |
| Setup / tooling / git / Husky / env | Matching `apps/DOCS/docs/setup/NN-*.md` |
| AI policy / agent workflow | `apps/DOCS/docs/ai/policy.md` + root `AI.md` when judgement calls matter |

**Do not** land convention-only rule changes without the matching doc page(s). If a convention spans FE + BE (e.g. `BE_ROUTES`), update **both** app docs.

## Shared DTOs (`libs/dtos/src/lib/<domain>/`)

Organize by **domain folder** (e.g. `user/`, not flat files at `lib/` root unless legacy).

| Suffix | Purpose | Example |
| ------ | ------- | ------- |
| **`.model.ts`** | Zod mirror of a **persisted** Mongoose model (stored shape only; no plaintext passwords) | `libs/dtos/src/lib/user/user.model.ts` |
| **`.dto.ts`** | Flow/API schemas (signup, login, responses, …) | `libs/dtos/src/lib/user/signup.dto.ts` |

- **Model DTO** (`.model.ts`) reflects what is stored in the database — not plaintext passwords or other transient input shapes.
- **Other DTOs** (`.dto.ts`) hold API/input validation (e.g. signup with plaintext password rules).
- Reuse shared Zod building blocks inside a domain (e.g. `password.schema.ts`) when multiple DTOs need the same rules — **do not invent new suffixes** (e.g. no `.fields.ts`; Developer reverted `user.fields.ts` from a `/simplify` pass).
- Some duplication between `.model.ts` and `.dto.ts` is acceptable; do not extract field schemas into unofficial file types.
- NestJS wraps shared schemas with `createZodDto` in `apps/BE` — keep wrappers in sync when adding schemas (see `apps/DOCS/docs/setup/06-nestjs-zod.md`).

## Mongoose (`mongoose/models/<domain>/`)

Per domain, always three files:

| File | Purpose |
| ---- | ------- |
| **`*.schema.ts`** | Mongoose schema + `model()` registration |
| **`*.model.ts`** | Repository interfaces (`IUser`, `IUserDocument`, …) |
| **`*.paths.ts`** | Field path constants for queries, projections, and schema keys |

### Why `*.paths.ts`?

**Never hard-code field strings** in queries — import from `*.paths.ts` so renames touch one file.

Example:

```ts
import { UserPaths } from '@quack/mongoose/models/user';

UserModel.findOne({ [UserPaths.email]: email });
```

### Mongoose directory (root)

```
mongoose/
├── client.ts          # DB connection (ENV_KEYS, E2E URI switch)
├── models/            # domain folders (user/, …)
├── fixtures/          # test/dev fixture data
└── tsconfig.json
```

## FE styling (Tailwind v4)

- **Nx scaffold** shipped Tailwind **v3** (`tailwind.config.js` + PostCSS); FE is migrated to **v4** (`tailwindcss@4`, `@tailwindcss/vite`).
- **Vite plugin** — `@tailwindcss/vite` in `apps/FE/vite.config.mts` (not PostCSS `tailwindcss` plugin).
- **CSS-first theme** — `apps/FE/src/styles.css`: `@import "tailwindcss"`, `@import "tw-animate-css"`, `@theme inline` for shadcn tokens; no `apps/FE/tailwind.config.js`.
- **shadcn CLI** — `apps/FE/components.json` with `"config": ""`; add components via `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add …` from `apps/FE`.

## FE dev tooling (development only)

- **[React Scan](https://react-scan.com/)** and **[React Grab](https://www.react-grab.com/)** — `dev-entry.ts` → `dev-tools.ts` (dev only) → `main.tsx`. Scan uses a static import in `dev-tools.ts` (must run before React); Grab uses dynamic `import()` there. Production entry skips `dev-tools` entirely.
- **React Scan** — visual re-render highlights for performance debugging.
- **React Grab** — ⌘C / Ctrl+C on a hovered element copies component context for coding agents.
- Docs: `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/frontend.md` — **Dev-only tooling**.

## FE HTTP client (`apps/FE/src/api/`)

- **One shared axios instance** — `axiosConfig.ts` exports the default client; **do not** call `axios.create()` elsewhere in FE.
- **`baseURL`** — from `VITE_API_URL` via `ENV_KEYS` (see `.env.example`); never hard-code API hosts in FE.
- **Import** — `import api from '@/api/axiosConfig'` (or relative `../axiosConfig` under `api/services/`).
- **`handleError.ts`** — normalizes `unknown` / `AxiosError` into `ErrorResponse` from `@shared/dtos`; axios-specific codes/messages live in `apps/FE/src/utils/constants.ts` (`AXIOS_ERROR_CODES`, `AXIOS_CONSTANTS`).
- **`services/`** — domain axios call sites (e.g. `authService.ts`); import `BE_ROUTES` from `@shared/constants` for path segments — **no magic route strings** in FE services.
- Interceptors (auth token, global errors) stay in `axiosConfig.ts` only.

## Backend routes (`libs/qu-constants/src/lib/be-routes.constants.ts`)

| Artifact | Purpose |
| -------- | ------- |
| **`BE_ROUTES` enum** | API path segments shared via `@shared/constants` |

- Define **every** BE endpoint path segment in `be-routes.constants.ts` — global prefix (`BASE`), controller segments (`USERS`, …), and action segments (`SIGNUP`, …).
- **No magic route strings** in controllers or `main.ts` — use `BE_ROUTES` in `@Controller`, `@Get`/`@Post`/…, and `setGlobalPrefix`.
- Place in `qu-constants` so the FE can import the same segments for API clients later.

## Backend feature modules (`apps/BE/src/<feature>/`)

| File | Purpose | Example |
| ---- | ------- | ------- |
| **`<feature>.controller.ts`** | HTTP routes for the feature | `users/users.controller.ts` |
| **`<feature>.dto.ts`** | `createZodDto` wrappers for that feature’s Zod schemas | `users/users.dto.ts` → `SignupDto` |
| **`<feature>.module.ts`** | Nest module wiring | `users/users.module.ts` |

- Colocate **DTO wrappers next to the controller** (`users/users.dto.ts`), not only in `app/app.dto.ts`.
- Shared Zod schemas stay in `libs/dtos`; BE wrappers import from `@shared/dtos`.

## Backend utilities (`apps/BE/src/utils/`)

| Location | Purpose | Example |
| -------- | ------- | ------- |
| **`*.util.ts`** | BE helpers (hashing, error parsing, …) | `password.util.ts`, `mongoose-error.handler.util.ts` |
| **`libs/<service>/`** | Wrappers for **external services** (S3, logger, email, …) | `utils/libs/s3/` |

- Do not use bare `utils/foo.ts` — use the **`.util.ts`** suffix.
- External SDK clients belong under `utils/libs/<domain-name-for-service>/`, not at `utils/` root.

## Imports

- `@shared/dtos`, `@shared/constants` from apps and `mongoose/`
- **`@quack/mongoose/*`** — repo Mongoose layer (`mongoose/` at repo root). **Do not** use deep relative imports (e.g. `../../../../mongoose/...`) or bare `mongoose/...` paths that collide with the npm `mongoose` package.
- App-local: `@/*` under `apps/FE` or `apps/BE`
- App tsconfigs: `baseUrl: "../.."` and extend `./tsconfig.json` (FE must keep `jsx`)

## Workflow

- New chat → `./scripts/next-quack-branch.sh <slug>` → `quack-XX-<slug>`
- Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, …) — enforced by commitlint; do not commit unless asked
- Verify with `pnpm check` or targeted `tsc` when touching types
